If you look at-- I mean, and
this issue is not specific

01:09:56.150 --> 01:10:00.670 position:56%
to copyright either if you hit the
buy button when you're buying a seat

01:10:00.670 --> 01:10:03.180
on an airplane, but I
don't think anybody thinks

01:10:03.180 --> 01:10:06.100
that they're actually
buying that seat.

01:10:06.100 --> 01:10:12.890 position:56%
And so, I think that terminology has
just been used because it's easier

01:10:12.890 --> 01:10:14.190
for consumers to understand.

01:10:14.190 --> 01:10:17.790
We talked about these sort of long
use and long licenses and it's

01:10:17.790 --> 01:10:20.960
so difficult for consumers
to understand.

01:10:20.960 --> 01:10:24.080
The idea is everyone is trying
to make it easier for consumers.

01:10:24.080 --> 01:10:27.540
And if you have these
long descriptions of the--

01:10:27.540 --> 01:10:32.250 position:56%
within the button I think that would
certainly make it more difficult.

01:10:32.250 --> 01:10:37.410
And then just the last thing I just
reiterate, which is already said.

01:10:37.410 --> 01:10:41.160
To the extent that the software
license is embedded in software--

01:10:41.160 --> 01:10:43.800
because remember, that's what
we're talking about here--

01:10:43.800 --> 01:10:50.030
are being misused or
abused, the market is

01:10:50.030 --> 01:10:51.800
and will be self-correcting.

01:10:51.800 --> 01:10:56.520
In our comments we mention
the Keurig example, OK?

01:10:56.520 --> 01:10:57.980
And that applies here.

01:10:57.980 --> 01:11:02.180
If you're engaging-- If a software

01:11:02.180 --> 01:11:04.420
or a hardware manufacturer
is engaging in sort

01:11:04.420 --> 01:11:08.030
of anti-consumer behavior, they're
not going to be around very long.

01:11:08.030 --> 01:11:12.810
And if the manufacturer is
dealing with a software company

01:11:12.810 --> 01:11:15.720
and that software company is just
trying to enforce their license

01:11:15.720 --> 01:11:17.350
in way that the manufacturer--

01:11:17.350 --> 01:11:20.820
device manufacturer isn't
particularly pleased with, well,

01:11:20.820 --> 01:11:23.020
that relationship is not going
to last very long either.

01:11:23.020 --> 01:11:26.990
So there are-- in terms of
the market and relationships,

01:11:26.990 --> 01:11:29.570
there are self-correcting
mechanisms in there

01:11:29.570 --> 01:11:32.800
if in fact these problems
were to continue to occur

01:11:32.800 --> 01:11:38.750
or can occur going into the future.

01:11:38.750 --> 01:11:40.640
&gt;&gt; Michelle Choe: Mr. Band.

01:11:40.640 --> 01:11:44.750 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Jonathan Band: So, a lot of
people have raised the issue of sort

01:11:44.750 --> 01:11:47.500
that there's this continuing
relationship

01:11:47.500 --> 01:11:52.850
that you're really not
getting a software as a product

01:11:52.850 --> 01:11:54.680
but a software as a device.

01:11:54.680 --> 01:11:59.560 position:56%
And that certainly might be true
