01:12:14.630 --> 01:12:20.300
But I think there's going to
be a lot of other software

01:12:20.300 --> 01:12:23.610
in the refrigerator and certainly
a lot of other software in the car,

01:12:23.610 --> 01:12:24.910
and all of these replaced--

01:12:24.910 --> 01:12:28.840 position:56%
all of these parts that Mr. Lowe has
been talking about that communicate

01:12:28.840 --> 01:12:33.790
with one another where they're
not interacting with, you know,

01:12:33.790 --> 01:12:38.300
with the cloud that they're just
interacting with other parts

01:12:38.300 --> 01:12:44.560
of the car and you'll have the
software that's interacting

01:12:44.560 --> 01:12:48.780
with other parts of
the refrigerator.

01:12:48.780 --> 01:12:55.720
And I think it's important to
sort of try to keep this issue--

01:12:55.720 --> 01:12:57.020
you know, keep those separate.

01:12:57.020 --> 01:12:59.820
Because I agree that if there
is an ongoing relationship

01:12:59.820 --> 01:13:01.840
that poses different issues.

01:13:01.840 --> 01:13:04.900
Now part of it, you know, there's
related issues like are you paying

01:13:04.900 --> 01:13:06.250
for the ongoing relationships?

01:13:06.250 --> 01:13:08.310
Certainly if you're
paying, you know,

01:13:08.310 --> 01:13:11.120
the subscription fee every
month, that's one thing.

01:13:11.120 --> 01:13:13.930
If there's a sort of a
paid-up license that--

01:13:13.930 --> 01:13:18.170
you know, paid-up license at the
beginning where it's understood

01:13:18.170 --> 01:13:21.540
that you're-- you know, for
the life of a refrigerator,

01:13:21.540 --> 01:13:24.470
it will always be communicating
with the cloud, you know,

01:13:24.470 --> 01:13:29.560
that might be different situation
and maybe in that case, you know,

01:13:29.560 --> 01:13:32.610
you have-- you know, the person

01:13:32.610 --> 01:13:35.680
about the refrigerator has a
different bundle of rights.

01:13:35.680 --> 01:13:39.940 position:56%
But it certainly seems to me that if
we're talking about sort of software

01:13:39.940 --> 01:13:44.940
that is-- you know, where there is
no ongoing relationship, I mean,

01:13:44.940 --> 01:13:48.180
that seems to be much easier case
to say, OK, let's figure out how

01:13:48.180 --> 01:13:49.680
to deal with that situation.

01:13:49.680 --> 01:13:52.650
In other words, you know,
there's a bit of a spectrum here,

01:13:52.650 --> 01:13:53.950
a spectrum of relationship.

01:13:53.950 --> 01:13:56.040
There could be situations
where there's absolutely none,

01:13:56.040 --> 01:13:59.320
there could be a situation where
there's a very tight relationship

01:13:59.320 --> 01:14:03.070
with the ongoing subscription,
and then you have situations

01:14:03.070 --> 01:14:04.810
in the middle where
there might be some sort

01:14:04.810 --> 01:14:07.100
of ongoing relationship
but it's all paid up.

01:14:07.100 --> 01:14:10.300
And those are three very different
situations that I think can be--

01:14:10.300 --> 01:14:11.600
&gt;&gt; Sy Damle: So do you think that--

01:14:11.600 --> 01:14:16.570
I mean, to me that suggest that we
should really careful about trying

01:14:16.570 --> 01:14:19.680
to be establish rules in this
area and that may be something

01:14:19.680 --> 01:14:23.300
that we should let courts sort
out on a case by case basis.

01:14:23.300 --> 01:14:25.560
I mean, do you disagree with that?

01:14:25.560 --> 01:14:26.860
&gt;&gt; Jonathan Band: Yes.

01:14:26.860 --> 01:14:31.180
Because I think it is
possible to come up with rules.

01:14:31.180 --> 01:14:35.100
Certainly where there is no
ongoing relationship, whatsoever,

01:14:35.100 --> 01:14:37.530
I think that's a very
easy case, you know,

01:14:37.530 --> 01:14:40.660
and we could come up
with rules today.

01:14:40.660 --> 01:14:41.960
And if fact, you know,

01:14:41.960 --> 01:14:45.540
to some extent that's what
[inaudible] tries to do that.

01:14:45.540 --> 01:14:47.740
It tried to be very careful.

01:14:47.740 --> 01:14:50.490
And one of the things that,
you know, in the conversations

01:14:50.490 --> 01:14:52.790
with Congressman Farenthold's
office that, you know,

01:14:52.790 --> 01:14:57.160
came up with exactly this but
what about the updates, right?

01:14:57.160 --> 01:15:00.530
And so there were some folks who
said, well, you know, if you--

01:15:00.530 --> 01:15:04.340
you know, and again we're only
dealing with the contemplations

01:15:04.340 --> 01:15:07.060
when you have a paid-up
license, when it's all--

01:15:07.060 --> 01:15:11.310
you know, you pay once
upfront, no ongoing payments.

01:15:11.310 --> 01:15:13.510
And so, should you be
when you sell it to the--

01:15:13.510 --> 01:15:19.610 position:56%
you know, when the device is sold to
the second person, what do they get

01:15:19.610 --> 01:15:24.930
in terms of software going forward?

01:15:24.930 --> 01:15:29.560
And there were some folks who were
very interested in saying, well,

01:15:29.560 --> 01:15:32.080
you should be able to get
whatever the first person

01:15:32.080 --> 01:15:35.240
or whatever the first purchaser
would have gotten if it had stayed

01:15:35.240 --> 01:15:36.780
in that person's possession.

01:15:36.780 --> 01:15:40.820
So, to the extent that there would
have been ongoing updates, then,

01:15:40.820 --> 01:15:44.360
you know, the second purchaser
should be able to get everything

01:15:44.360 --> 01:15:48.310
that the first purchaser had
bought-- would have gotten.

01:15:48.310 --> 01:15:53.040
But actually, you know,
the ultimate conclusion--

01:15:53.040 --> 01:15:58.630
again, not necessarily that
our numbers would have wanted--

01:15:58.630 --> 01:16:05.540
was that now you only got bug
fixes and security patches.

01:16:05.540 --> 01:16:11.020
You don't get the new releases,
so that-- you know, that there's--

01:16:11.020 --> 01:16:14.350 position:56%
that you are-- even though you would
have paid upfront and if it stayed

01:16:14.350 --> 01:16:17.330
with the first person that would
have gotten any new release,

01:16:17.330 --> 01:16:21.150
the idea is that, you
know, because the sense was

01:16:21.150 --> 01:16:23.250
that there is this ongoing
relationship and it's sort

01:16:23.250 --> 01:16:28.620
of different that you don't get
the full bundle you get less.

01:16:28.620 --> 01:16:31.100 position:56%
But the point is that these are ones

01:16:31.100 --> 01:16:33.900
that Congress is perfectly
capable of drawing.

01:16:33.900 --> 01:16:36.370
&gt;&gt; Sy Damle: That line
seems particular--

01:16:36.370 --> 01:16:40.260
That seems like a very difficult
