01:17:00.450 --> 01:17:01.750
that would be great.

01:17:01.750 --> 01:17:04.050 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Sy Damle: I mean, you know, but
that again goes back to the question

01:17:04.050 --> 01:17:06.360
of whether there's like
a practical concern here.

01:17:06.360 --> 01:17:08.510
I mean, you know, just
looking on eBay to see

01:17:08.510 --> 01:17:10.630 position:56%
if I can buy a used Nest thermostat.

01:17:10.630 --> 01:17:11.930
And you can.

01:17:11.930 --> 01:17:15.940
And I'm not-- So going again
to the fact that this is

01:17:15.940 --> 01:17:19.850
about consumer products
if there is not problem--

01:17:19.850 --> 01:17:22.390
a demonstrated problem
in the marketplace,

01:17:22.390 --> 01:17:25.720
I'm not sure just looking it
from Congress' perspective

01:17:25.720 --> 01:17:28.200
that they're particularly would
be interested in trying to jump

01:17:28.200 --> 01:17:30.420
into this kind of thorny issue.

01:17:30.420 --> 01:17:34.370
So again, just to reiterate to the
