backward but in terms

01:22:32.200 --> 01:22:35.010
of how it applies looking
forward into the areas

01:22:35.010 --> 01:22:39.010 position:56%
where consumers have no expectation,
whatsoever, of licensing

01:22:39.010 --> 01:22:42.310
and whether there is no history
of a practice of licensing.

01:22:42.310 --> 01:22:45.470
To come back to Keith's
point, the great thing

01:22:45.470 --> 01:22:48.110
about doing empirical research
is you don't have to suppose

01:22:48.110 --> 01:22:50.650
or imagine you get like
answers to questions.

01:22:50.650 --> 01:22:55.000
And it turns out that young white
men are in fact more confused

01:22:55.000 --> 01:22:57.970
than anyone about what
the Buy Now button means,

01:22:57.970 --> 01:23:01.500
and it turns out that providing
a bullet-pointed short notice

01:23:01.500 --> 01:23:03.450
significantly reduces the degree

01:23:03.450 --> 01:23:05.670
to which consumers
misunderstand the rights.

01:23:05.670 --> 01:23:11.600
The papers up on SSRN, if anybody's
interested, I recommend you read it

01:23:11.600 --> 01:23:15.210
because I do think there is
value from having real evidence

01:23:15.210 --> 01:23:18.110
and not just imagining
the way the role might be.

